<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>The "bad" at Venturebeat (and Torrentfreak and Techdirt) outweighs the good, even before you consider that a bad story is more harmful to HN than a good story is helpful.<p>On those occasions where Venturebeat gets it right, someone will inevitably blog it. The blog posts won't get banned. People will find out about the article. Meanwhile, Venturebeat has that much less incentive to directly troll HN.<p>I have zero illusions that Venturebeat is going to get banned. The incentives are wrong for Paul Graham. Venturebeat writes more positive stuff about YC companies than negative stuff. But if Graham is serious about Venturebeat trolling the site --- which it clearly does, all the time --- he shouldn't be choosy about pushing back on it.</font></span><p><font size=1><u><a href="reply?id=3530541&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%67%43%6f%77%50%69%71%37%50%73">reply</a></u></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=80></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3530558 href="vote?for=3530558&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%67%43%6f%77%50%69%71%37%50%73"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3530558></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=nicholasjbs">nicholasjbs</a> 6 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3530558">link</a></span></div><br>
